WEBVTT

03:11.800 --> 03:16.560
The Alexandria, was found adrift
at 1,200 miles from the Chilean coast

03:16.639 --> 03:19.479
by a Japanese fishing ship
that went to its rescue.

03:19.560 --> 03:22.879
It had spent weeks
in the waters of the South Pacific.

03:23.360 --> 03:27.159
<i>The ship was undertaking</i>
<i>scientific research,</i>

03:27.240 --> 03:29.840
<i>therefore,</i>
<i>the details of which are unknown.</i>

03:30.360 --> 03:32.599
<i>The authorities have confirmed</i>

03:32.680 --> 03:36.560
<i>that one of the Alexandria's passengers</i>
<i>has been found alive.</i>

03:36.879 --> 03:41.000
<i>The survivor is expected,</i>
<i>who is being transferred to Valparaíso,</i>

03:41.080 --> 03:42.800
<i>to clarify what happened.</i>

39:39.719 --> 39:41.239
The mystery of the Alexandria,

39:41.320 --> 39:43.440
which was found adrift
in the South Pacific Ocean,

39:43.519 --> 39:46.880
is soon to be solved
after the sole survivor has made it

39:46.960 --> 39:48.599
to the Valparaíso naval hospital.

39:49.280 --> 39:52.440
We've been informed
that the survivor is not in danger,

39:52.519 --> 39:54.320
and is waiting to speak to the Police.

39:54.400 --> 39:56.719
The identity of the survivor
hasn't been revealed.

39:58.800 --> 40:01.079
Come on, move.
She's lost a lot of blood! Hurry!
